  "text": "Input stimuli: The basic idea was to have periodic environmental stimuli based on a sine curve (shifted to the interval [0, 1]). The wavelength w was set to 20 time steps, while the lifetime L for every GRN was 400 steps. Variations included having only the positive part of sine, a periodic step function, and a brief pulse. The four functions used are depicted in fig. 5 . The impact of Gaussian noise and blackout periods in the input during evolution was investigated in earlier experiments published elsewhere [CITATION_1] . As mentioned above, both cells of an individual always received the same periodic stimuli, however one cell additionally received an inducing signal with a value of 1.",
